  "prompt": "What are the best book in preparation for bank exams?",
  "response": "Preparing for bank exams requires a comprehensive understanding of various topics, including quantitative aptitude, reasoning, English language, general awareness, and banking/financial awareness. Here are some of the most recommended books for each section:\n\n### **Quantitative Aptitude**\n1. **\"Quantitative Aptitude for Competitive Examinations\" by R.S. Aggarwal**  \n   - Covers all the essential topics with a good number of practice questions.\n   \n2. **\"Fast Track Objective Arithmetic\" by Rajesh Verma (Arihant Publications)**  \n   - Focuses on shortcuts and tricks to solve problems quickly.\n\n### **Reasoning Ability**\n1. **\"A Modern Approach to Verbal & Non-Verbal Reasoning\" by R.S. Aggarwal**  \n   - Comprehensive coverage of both verbal and non-verbal reasoning topics.\n\n2. **\"Analytical Reasoning\" by M.K. Pandey**  \n   - Specifically helpful for advanced reasoning questions.\n\n### **English Language**\n1. **\"Objective General English\" by S.P. Bakshi (Arihant Publications)**  \n   - Covers grammar, vocabulary, and comprehension with practice exercises.\n\n2. **\"High School English Grammar & Composition\" by Wren & Martin**  \n   - A classic book for improving grammar and writing skills.\n\n### **General Awareness**\n1. **\"Lucent's General Knowledge\"**  \n   - A concise and well-structured book for static GK.\n\n2. **\"Manorama Yearbook\"**  \n   - Provides updated information on current affairs and general knowledge.\n\n### **Banking & Financial Awareness**\n1. **\"Banking Awareness\" by Arihant Publications**  \n   - Covers all the essential topics related to banking and financial awareness.\n\n2. **\"Banking Awareness Handbook\" by Disha Experts**  \n   - A compact book focusing on key banking terms and concepts.\n\n### **Mock Tests & Previous Year Papers**\n1. **\"Bank PO Previous Year Papers\" by Kiran Prakashan**  \n   - Provides solved previous year question papers to understand the exam pattern.\n\n2. **\"Test Series for Bank Exams\" by Adda247 or Gradeup**  \n   - Online test series that simulate the actual exam environment.\n\n### **Additional Resources**\n- **Newspapers:** **The Hindu**, **Economic Times** for current affairs and editorials.\n- **Magazines:** **Pratiyogita Darpan**, **Competition Success Review** for current affairs and GK.\n- **Online Platforms:** **Adda247**, **Gradeup**, **Testbook** for practice tests, quizzes, and video lessons.\n\nBy using these resources and consistently practicing, you can prepare effectively for bank exams. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
